.sp
In CMake 3.28 and below, \fI\%add_test()\fP unconditionally used the
\fI\%CROSSCOMPILING_EMULATOR\fP target property (initialized by the
\fI\%CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING_EMULATOR\fP variable) to run test commands
naming executable targets.  CMake 3.29 and above prefer to use the emulator
only when the \fI\%CMAKE_CROSSCOMPILING\fP variable is enabled.  The
\fI\%CMAKE_TEST_LAUNCHER\fP variable may be used instead when not
cross\-compiling.  This policy provides compatibility for projects that
have not been updated.
.sp
